oc:kn_13e9c3aa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When applying data quality flag filters to any light curve" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Quality flag conventions are NOT universal: flag=0 may mean GOOD (TESS standard) or BAD (some exported formats). Always verify which convention your data source uses." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incorrect flag interpretation inverts the filter, removing all good data and keeping bad data" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_269d45c8 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting outlier removal and flattening parameters" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sigma values: σ=2 aggressive (removes ~5%), σ=3 standard (removes ~0.3%), σ=5 conservative (removes fewer points). Window lengths: 100-200 short trends, 300-500 medium/TESS, 500-1000 long trends." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Provides reasonable starting parameters that can be tuned based on data characteristics" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4b877361 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Standard lightkurve preprocessing pipeline" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """lc_clean, mask = lc.remove_outliers(sigma=3, return_mask=True)
lc_flat = lc_clean.flatten(window_length=500)""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Canonical lightkurve API for outlier removal and detrending" .

oc:kn_6445c735 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When considering iterative sine fitting for stellar variability removal" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Iterative sine fitting removes periodic signals — use with extreme caution when searching for periodic transits" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each iteration removes the dominant remaining periodic component, which could be the transit signal itself" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_77c2e302 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Building a preprocessing pipeline for exoplanet transit detection" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Apply data quality flags to remove bad cadences 2. Remove outliers via sigma clipping (σ=3–5) 3. Flatten long-term trends with Savitzky-Golay filter (window_length=100–1000 depending on data) 4. Optional second-pass outlier removal on detrended residuals" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Order matters: quality flags remove systematic bad data, then outlier removal before detrending prevents outliers from biasing the trend model, and flattening preserves transit shapes" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_9ef578aa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "lightkurve, numpy, and matplotlib must be installed (pip install lightkurve numpy matplotlib)" .

oc:kn_c188e38b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting flatten() window_length parameter" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Flattening window_length must be longer than the expected transit duration but shorter than the stellar rotation period" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Window too short removes the transit signal itself; window too long fails to remove the stellar variability trend" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_cccaf3ed a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before applying quality flag filtering" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify quality flag convention for your data source before filtering. Check which approach (flag==0 or flag!=0) yields cleaner results." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Prevents catastrophic data loss from inverted flag logic" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_cf5122ed a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When tuning preprocessing parameters for transit detection" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never apply aggressive preprocessing (low sigma, short window lengths, multiple iterations of sine fitting) when searching for shallow transits — it will remove real signals" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-processing is the most common cause of missed exoplanet detections; transit signals are shallow, short-duration dips easily removed by aggressive smoothing" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_d47f57a6 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When any preprocessing step filters or transforms data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include flux_err in all preprocessing outputs — it is critical for proper weighting in downstream period search algorithms (BLS, Lomb-Scargle, TLS)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Period search algorithms weight data points by uncertainty; discarding error information degrades detection sensitivity" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_dd7da208 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After each preprocessing step (outlier removal, flattening, quality filtering)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Plot the light curve before and after each major preprocessing step to verify data quality is improving and real signals are preserved" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Visual inspection catches over-processing, incorrect parameters, and removed transit signals that statistics alone may miss" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e3f3ba28 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When removing dominant stellar variability components iteratively" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """def sine_fitting(lc):
    pg = lc.to_periodogram()
    model = pg.model(time=lc.time, frequency=pg.frequency_at_max_power)
    lc_new = lc.copy()
    lc_new.flux = lc_new.flux / model.flux
    return lc_new, model""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Removes high-frequency stellar variability (rotation, pulsation) that Savitzky-Golay may not fully capture" .

